==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Madhouse
<hw>Mad"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
house or institution where insane persons are confined; an insane
asylum; a bedlam; -- usually used in a deprecatory sense.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Bedlam, booby hatch, crazy house, cuckoo's nest,
funny farm, funny house, insane asylum, loony bin, nuthouse,
sanatorium.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(fig.)</mark> <def>A
chaotic, raucus or highly disordered situation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
